FuncDef: The display nat64 alg server-list command displays the list of NAT64 ALG IPv4 server addresses for application layer protocols.
CLIs: display nat64 alg server-list protocol { all | dns | ftp | http }

ParaDef.Info:
Displays the list of NAT64 ALG IPv4 server addresses for all application layer protocols.
-

Displays the list of NAT64 ALG IPv4 server addresses for DNS.
-

Displays the list of NAT64 ALG IPv4 server addresses for FTP.
-

Displays the list of NAT64 ALG IPv4 server addresses for HTTP.
-

Examples: <HUAWEI> display nat64 alg server-list protocol all
ExtraInfo: After a list of NAT64 ALG IPv4 server addresses for application layer protocols is configured, to view information about the list for a specific or all application layer protocols, run the display nat64 alg server-list protocol command.
